Description.1: Riverview Farmers Market is a seasonal Sunday market in the Heights neighborhood of Jersey City. We are a thriving, community-supported, producer-first farmers market, offering a wide range of market vendors and goods which serves all community members, and which especially supports small, local family farmers. We are also a gathering place where the diverse population of Jersey City Heights can get nourishment for their minds, as well as their bodies, through art, music and kids programming. Our market runs every Sunday, May through November, 10 AM to 2PM. We are located in Riverview Fisk Park.

Description.10: The mission of the nonprofit Hunterdon Land Trust is to preserve the integrity of the rural landscapes in the Hunterdon County region by protecting and enhancing natural resources, and the cultural landscape of the historic Dvoor Farm, for public enjoyment and education. From May to late November, we operate a Farmers' Market every Sunday, 9 a.m.-1 p.m. at the historic Dvoor Farm in Flemington.
